text:
Data Scientist



<a href="mailto:Jonathanoliphant13@gmail.com">Jonathanoliphant13@gmail.com</a>
<span>385 452 1364</span>
<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathanoliphantb300b42ab">LinkedIn</a>




Anticipated: July 2027
Brigham Young University - Idaho
Bachelor of Science; Data Science
GPA: 4.0



SQL

Designed and implemented relational databases, establishing efficient data structures.
Extracted and analyzed complex datasets to answer diverse business questions utilizing advanced queries, subqueries, and Common Table Expressions (CTEs).
Collaborated with a team to architect and build a functional database schema for a fictional business, gaining practical experience in database design.

Applied Calculus for Data Analysis

Applied differentiation techniques to identify critical data points and inform predictive modeling strategies.
Utilized integration to compute probability of various continuous random variables.
Leveraged R and Mathematica to solve complex mathematical problems, enhancing computational problem-solving skills for data analysis.

Data Intuitions and Insight

Developed compelling data visualizations using Tableau to identify trends and communicate insights effectively.
Prepared and delivered data-driven presentations, translating raw data into clear, actionable insights for non-technical audiences.

Programming with Functions

Developed Python programs to efficiently read, process, and organize external datasets, laying groundwork for data pipeline understanding.

Introduction to Cybersecurity

Gained foundational understanding of cybersecurity principles, including terminal navigation and exploring file systems within virtual machine environments, relevant for data security contexts.






September 2023 - Present
Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, ID
Accessibility Specialist Team Lead

Conducted thorough audits of university courses to ensure accessibility compliance, leading to the development of accessible video and document versions for diverse users.
Met with other team leads to increase productivity and morale of employees in the office.
Trained new hires on accessibility principles and overall workflow.
Worked with AI to build scripts using JavaScript and increased efficiency of the team.





Programming Languages: Python, SQL, R
Data Analysis & Visualization Tools: Tableau, MySQL, Mathematica
Concepts & Tools: Data Exploration, Database Management, Virtual Machines, Terminal Navigation, AI-Assisted Programming
